
// The code snippet demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to perform addition operations on nodes retrieved from a data source. It uses [get-nodes] to obtain the values of [limit] and [offset] from the [.arguments] node, and adds these values to the result of a [data.read] operation. This is useful for dynamically adjusting data retrieval parameters based on input arguments.
add:x:./*/data.read
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/limit
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/offset
